{
  "texts": [
    "When only the first three years of data are considered, these numbers drop to 13, 19, and 50 epochs.",
    "The first set aims to evaluate EzTaoX's ability to recover interband lags (see Section 3.1.2), and the light curves consist of simulated LSST observations in g and r bands.",
    "The g-r lag for each multiband light curve is uniformly sampled between 0.01 day and 10 days, while the input g-band τ DRW and σ DRW are fixed at fiducial values of 100 days and 0.112 mag, respectively.",
    "These choices of τ DRW and σ DRW are representative of those measured from typical quasar (i.e., high luminosity AGN) UV/optical light curves (e.g., Vanden Berk et al. 2004; MacLeod et al. 2010).",
    "The second set tests EzTaoX's ability to recover the DRW characteristic timescale τ DRW (see Section 3.1.3), and the light curves consist of simulated LSST observations in u, g, and r bands."
  ]
}